docs.snippet: THE REPORTED CHILD-MURDER CASE--An inquest was held yesterday at No. 355 West Twenty-sixty-street upon the body of CATHARINE STACKPOLE, a child three months old, who was reported to have been killed by her father.

headline.main: HAVANA.; Arrival of the Black Warrior.

docs.lead_paragraph: The U. S. Mail steamship Black Warrior, J. W. SMITH Commander, from New-Orleans 12th and Havana 15th, at 10 o'clock A. M., arrived at this port yesterday. The Black Warrior has experienced very heavy weather from the northward and eastward since leaving Havana.

docs.lead_paragraph: The steamship Pacific, of the North Atlantic Steamship Company's Line, from Galway, on the morning of Oct. 13, arrived at St. Johns, Newfoundland, yesterday morning. Her advices are three days later than those by the Europa. She reports that the equinoctial gales had (lone serious damage, attended with loss of life, to the shipping in the North Sea.
